snippet.textDisplay: I loved to see you doing this! I'm vegan for a couple months now because of animal cruelty reasons and it can be hard! Before that I was vegetarian when I got well informed about the whole diary industry I realised that being just vegetarian wasn't enough. snippet.textDisplay:
You went plant based for 30 days.

Veganism is ETHICS, not diet. We eat plant based diets, and have a philosophy called veganism.

Important distinction. Vegans don't wear leather , ride horses or use products tested on animals. It's not about nutrition.

Note: I am not trying to give you shit, just to make it clear. I just see the terms used interchangeably, when they are in fact, not, so I like to let people know.
snippet.textOriginal:
You went *plant based* for 30 days.

Veganism is ETHICS, not diet.  We eat plant based diets, and have a  *philosophy* called veganism.

Important distinction. Vegans don't wear leather , ride horses or use products tested on animals. It's not about nutrition.

Note: I am not trying to give you shit, just to make it clear. I just see the terms used interchangeably, when they are in fact, not, so I like to let people know.
